<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_occurrence_mim  Rule: restrict_part_occurrence_category 
   <express_ref linkend="product_occurrence:mim:Product_occurrence_mim.restrict_part_occurrence_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_occurrence_mim.restrict_part_occurrence_category">
The <b>restrict_part_occurrence_category</b> rule constrains the category of every instance of <b>product_definition</b> of type 'part_occurrence'.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_occurrence_mim.restrict_part_occurrence_category.wr:WR1">
Every instance of <b>product_definition</b> of type 'part_occurrence' shall be categorised as either 'part','raw material' or 'tool'.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_occurrence_mim  Function: types_of_product 
   <express_ref linkend="product_occurrence:mim:Product_occurrence_mim.types_of_product"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_occurrence_mim.types_of_product">
The function <b>types_of_product</b> accepts a product and returns a set of strings which are the set of all the category names of the related products.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_occurrence_mim.types_of_product.obj">identifies the considered product</ext_description>

